Opportunities



Store
Our Retail stores are constantly evolving, but the Lowe’s commitment to our customers never changes. Follow your passion and build your career at one of more than 2,370 Lowe’s stores across North America.

Learn More  about Store


Corporate
When you join Lowe’s Corporate Support Center, you’ll be part of a dynamic team that supports our Retail Stores and our Distribution Centers. Build an exciting career here. 

Learn More  about Corporate


Distribution
Our Distribution Centers keep our retail stores stocked so our customer’s home improvement dreams can come true – project after project. Join our efficient team and embark on a moving career.

Learn More  about Distribution







Why Lowe's

Looking for a company that's dedicated to its employees and their growth?
Lowe’s owes its success to its dedicated employees – employees who enjoy helping people love where they live. Their desire to make things happen has made Lowe’s a leader in home improvement. We believe that creating a diverse and inclusive work environment as well as one that rewards employees for their contributions and hard work is essential for our continued success. That’s why we offer employees the opportunities they need to succeed both personally and professionally. Our comprehensive benefits and expansive learning and development programs together with a variety of career options make Lowe’s an exceptional place to begin and grow your career. 

Most Admired Company 2015 Fortune
10 Happiest Retailers to Work For 2014


Go  find more about Looking for a company that's dedicated to its employees and their growth?






Military

Are you a military veteran? Reservist? Spouse?
Your skills and experience work here. Use our Military Skills Translator to find a Lowe’s opportunity that’s a perfect fit for you. 
The military instills leadership, a strong work ethic, and a passion for a job well done, a testament to the “Power of We.” The founder of Lowe’s, Carl Buchan is a military veteran himself. Today, Lowe’s employs more than 13,000 military veterans across our organization, in fields from management, IT and retail to customer service. We continue to pursue military veterans, reservists and military spouses to join our team by participating in a variety of military-sponsored programs and events across the country.

Military Friendly Employer 2014
ESGR
Military Spouse EP


Go  find more about Are you a military veteran? Reservist? Spouse?






Diversity

Why we embrace diversity & inclusion.
Lowe’s is committed to a workplace culture that leverages diverse talent to create innovative solutions.   Our employees thrive in an environment where everyone can reach their full potential and provide our customers with  a great shopping experience.
To support our commitment to maintain a diverse workforce, Lowe’s participates in several career conferences that engage diverse candidates such as the National Black MBA Conference, and Women of Color STEM Conference (Science, Technology, Engineering & Mathematics). Check out our Conference & Event calendar to see if we have an upcoming event near you.

2014 Champions Honoree - National Inclusion Project


Go  find more about Why we embrace diversity & inclusion.






On Campus

Still in school? Recently graduated?
Undergraduate Graduate Recent Graduate
Kick-start or grow your career at Lowe’s.
As a home improvement company, Lowe’s knows the importance of building on a solid foundation. Higher education is often the foundation for a great career. Whether you’re in school and looking for an internship or a recent graduate, chances are Lowe’s has the perfect opportunity for you to learn and grow your career at one of our Contact, Corporate or Distribution centers or at a Lowe’s store. We also believe that learning doesn’t stop outside the classroom – that’s why we offer our employees a variety of training and development programs along with career opportunities where they can continue to learn. From interior design consultation or landscaping design, we encourage our employees to develop their knowledge and skills so they can help our customers love where they live. 

Go  find more about Still in school? Recently graduated?






