LOWE'S COMPANIES, INC. Revenue and Financial Data

Lowe's Companies has evolved from a regional hardware store into a nationwide chain of home improvement superstores bent on international expansion. The #2 US home improvement chain (after The Home Depot), Lowe's operates 1,820 stores in the US, along with some 300 in Canada, and 10 in Mexico, as well as an e-commerce site. Its stores sell roughly 37,000 products for DIY-ers and professionals for home improvement and repair projects, such as lumber, paint, plumbing and electrical supplies, tools, and gardening products, as well as appliances, outdoor power equipment, home fashions and furniture. Lowe's is also the second-largest US home appliance retailer after Sears.
  







