Lowe's Companies, Inc owns and operates retail home improvement centers across the United States. Lowe's stocks over forty thousand home improvement products and offers many more by special order.  Lowe's owns and operates 1,857 superstores in North America (1725 Lowe's Hardware… MoreLowe's Companies, Inc owns and operates retail home improvement centers across the United States. Lowe's stocks over forty thousand home improvement products and offers many more by special order.  Lowe's owns and operates 1,857 superstores in North America (1725 Lowe's Hardware stores in the US, 80 Orchard Supply stores in California and Oregon, 42 stores in Canada, and 10 in Mexico) as well as an e-commerce site.  The company expects to add approximately 45 new stores in 2016.  Lowe's employs approximately 180,000 full-time employees and 90,000 part-time employees.

Lowe's owns one third of Masters Home Improvement, a joint venture with Woolworths Limited based in Australia, but is in the process of exiting its investment in the joint venture.  Lowe's Companies Canada and Orchard Supply Hardware are profiled separately in RainKing.

Lowe's acquired RONA, Inc. in May, 2016.
Lowe's partners with BNSF Logistics for transportation.


IT Priorities:
• Lowe's Companies, Inc. is currently engaged in a large-scale insourcing program, part of a larger industry trend which has included Target, AstraZeneca, DeutscheBank, and GM.  The primary focus of this project has… MoreLowe's partners with BNSF Logistics for transportation.


IT Priorities:
• Lowe's Companies, Inc. is currently engaged in a large-scale insourcing program, part of a larger industry trend which has included Target, AstraZeneca, DeutscheBank, and GM.  The primary focus of this project has been a buildout of Lowe's operations in Bengaluru, India.
• The company has a $100,000-$500,000 application testing contract up for renewal in 2016.
• Mobile applications development is expected to remain a focus throughout 2016.
• Lowe's Innovation Labs is currently partnering with startups in India focused on HR workforce automation, online search solutions, and 3D printing.


IT Structure:
• The IT department for Lowe's Companies, Inc. is primarily based at the corporate headquarters in Mooresville, NC, though much of the IT staff is divided between several locations such as Winston Salem, NC, and North Wilkesboro, NC.
• Data Center is located in Winston Salem, NC.
• Lowe's currently has IT outsourcing contracts with Infosys and Wipro in India, and Cognizant in the US.
• Lowe's uses iPhones for in-store mobile support, and has a long-term contract with Apple.



IT Snippets:
2016:
• The company plans to reduce outsourcing spending, in favor of insourcing.  This will include doubling staff at the Global In-house Center (GIC) in Bengaluru by the end of 2016, to a total of approximately 900 employees.
 





